quran[75]{c,v,t}:
  87,1,"Glorify the Name of your Lord, the Most High"
  87,2,"Who has created, and then proportioned it"
  87,3,And Who has measured; and then guided
  87,4,And Who brings out the pasturage
  87,5,And then makes it dark stubble
  87,6,"We shall make you recite, so you shall not forget"
  87,7,Except what Allah may will He knows what is apparent and what is hidden
  87,8,And We shall make easy for you the easy
  87,9,Therefore remind in case the reminder profits
  87,10,The reminder will be received by him who fears
  87,11,But it will be avoided by the wretched
  87,12,Who will enter the great Fire
  87,13,There he will neither die nor live
  87,14,Indeed whosoever purifies himself shall achieve success
  87,15,"And remembers the Name of his Lord, and performs Salah"
  87,16,Rather you prefer the life of this world
  87,17,Although the Hereafter is better and more lasting
  87,18,"Verily, this is in the former Scriptures"
  87,19,The Scriptures of Ibrahim and Musa
  88,1,Has there come to you the narration of Al-Ghashiyah (the overwhelming)
  88,2,Some faces that Day will be Khashi`ah
  88,3,"Laboring, weary"
  88,4,"They will enter into Fire, Hamiyah"
  88,5,They will be given to drink from a boiling (Aniyah) spring
  88,6,No food will there be for them but from Dari
  88,7,Which will neither nourish nor avail against hunger
  88,8,Faces that Day will be joyful
  88,9,Glad with their endeavor
  88,10,In a lofty Paradise
  88,11,Where they shall neither hear harmful speech nor falsehood
  88,12,Therein will be a running spring
  88,13,Therein will be thrones raised high
  88,14,And cups set at hand
  88,15,"And Namariq, set in rows"
  88,16,"And Zarabi, spread out (Mabthuthah)"
  88,17,"Do they not look at the camels, how they are created"
  88,18,"And at the heaven, how it is raised"
  88,19,"And at the mountains, how they are rooted"
  88,20,"And at the earth, how it is outspread"
  88,21,So remind them -- you are only one who reminds
  88,22,You are not a Musaytir over them
  88,23,Save the one who turns away and disbelieves
  88,24,Then Allah will punish him with the greatest punishment
  88,25,"Verily, to Us will be their return"
  88,26,"Then verily, for Us will be their reckoning"
  89,1,By the dawn
  89,2,And by the ten nights
  89,3,And by the even and the odd
  89,4,And by the night when it departs
  89,5,Is there (not) in them sufficient proofs for men of understanding
  89,6,Saw you not how your Lord dealt with `Ad
  89,7,Iram of the pillars
  89,8,The like of which were not created in the land
  89,9,"And Thamud, who hewed out rocks in the valley"
  89,10,And Fir`awn with Al-Awtad
  89,11,Who did transgress beyond bounds in the lands
  89,12,And made therein much mischief
  89,13,"So, your Lord poured on them different kinds of severe torment"
  89,14,"Verily, your Lord is Ever Watchful"
  89,15,"As for man, when his Lord tries him by giving him honor and bounties, then he says: \"My Lord has honored me"
  89,16,"But when He tries him by straitening his means of life, he says: \"My Lord has humiliated me"
  89,17,But no! But you treat not the orphans with kindness and generosity
  89,18,And urge not one another on the feeding of the Miskin
  89,19,And you devour the Turath -- devouring with greed
  89,20,And you love wealth with love Jamma
  89,21,"Nay! When the earth is flatened, Dakkan Dakka"
  89,22,And your Lord comes with the angels in rows
  89,23,"And Hell will be brought near that Day. On that Day will man remember, but how will that remembrance avail him"
  89,24,"He will say: \"Alas! Would that I had sent forth for my life"
  89,25,So on that Day none will punish as He will punish
  89,26,And none will bind as He will bind
  89,27,O tranquil soul
  89,28,"Come back to your Lord, -- well-pleased and well-pleasing"
  89,29,Enter then among My servants
  89,30,And enter My Paradise